RACE.RACE_TEXT: FanDuel Racing Pacific Classic S. - Grade1 DEL MAR RACE 10 1 1/4M Dirt CR: 110. Stakes Purse 1000000. FOR THREE-YEAR-OLDS AND UPWARD.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ARABIAN KNIGHT sped to the front staying well off the rail, angled into the two path entering the first turn then moved inside, showed the way to the far turn, met the challenge from SLOW DOWN ANDY around the bend and dueled into the lane, battled into the final furlong, cleared that rival at the sixteenth pole but was soon tested by GEAUX ROCKET RIDE and gamely prevailed. GEAUX ROCKET RIDE broke alertly, stalked the pace along the inside, tipped three wide past the quarter pole, moved out further in upper stretch, launched a bid from outside in the final sixteenth but could not get by the winner. SLOW DOWN ANDY was keen early on when rated, chasing off the inside, rounded the clubhouse turn four then three wide, tugged forward on the backstretch to move up outside the top pair, challenged ARABIAN KNIGHT three wide on the far turn, battled down the lane but faltered in the final sixteenth. SENOR BUSCADOR tracked off the inside in the early going, moved out wider on the backstretch, rounded the far turn five wide then came six wide into the stretch, summoned a mild rally and earned a minor award. SKINNER sat off the pace three then two wide early, ridden along while angling in on the far turn, steered out in the lane and improved position. DEFUNDED was caught five wide outside a rival entering the clubhouse then moved into the four path around the bend, drifted in a bit and was corrected at the seven-sixteenths pole, spun four wide into the lane and weakened. PIROLI raced up close outside the leader first time through the stretch then took a stalking position, flanked the pacesetter in the middle stages, was all out while losing ground around the far turn and weakened in the lane. TRIPOLI settled inside early, moved into range up the backstretch, asked left-handed on the far turn but started to weaken and came up empty in the drive. ORDER AND LAW traveled two wide then moved inside racing near the back, continued to save ground on the far turn, eased in the lane and walked off. STILLETO BOY shifted and came away awkwardly in the beginning, unhurried and moved inside, steered off the rail on the clubhouse turn, chased between foes leaving the backstretch, tired four wide around the far turn, eased through the lane and walked off.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Del Mar H. Presented by The Japan Racing Association - Grade2 DEL MAR RACE 11 1 3/8M Turf CR: 108. Stakes Purse 300000. FOR THREE-YEAR-OLDS AND UPWARD.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GOLD PHOENIX (IRE) settled in the two path near the back, found traffic on the far turn, angled five wide, rallied between rivals in the lane, drew alongside the leader in deep stretch and drove clear. NINEELEVENTURBO broke well then ceded command to the top pair and took a stalking position on the inside, moved off the rail for the final turn, launched a bid three deep, took over at the three-sixteenths pole, cleared in upper stretch, yielded to the winner in deep stretch and saved second. CASH EQUITY (FR) traveled three then two wide near the back early, traveled three deep into the last turn, swung seven wide into the stretch, finished well but missed the place. MISSED THE CUT unhurried in the two path then moved inside, chased within striking distance between rivals leaving the backstretch, spun three wide into the lane, given his cue at the top of the stretch, rallied between rivals but was outkicked in the late stages. PLANETARIO (BRZ) rated in the two path, moved closer three deep into the last turn, rallied four deep around the bend and got outkicked in the furlong grounds. CATHKIN PEAK (IRE) pulled while reserved early and moved inside, swung eight wide leaving the final bend and was forced to take up late. OFFLEE NAUGHTY trailed in the early going, traveled three deep up the backstretch, rallied four, five then six wide on the final turn and flattened out. NONE ABOVE THE LAW rated along the inside out of range early, drew closer on the backstretch, waited for room on the far turn, tipped out and asked in upper stretch but also flattened. WIN THE DAY reserved on the inside early, lacked room from the three-eighths pole to the quarter pole, gained a clear path while remaining next to the fence, ran into traffic once again in upper stretch, tipped out and could not rally. CROSBY BEACH dueled for the lead from inside then took control first time through the lane, pressured from outside up the backstretch, challenged by rivals around the far turn, relinquished the lead at the quarter pole and retreated in the stretch run. AZUL COAST dueled from outside on the first turn, ceded command to CROSBY BEACH in the stretch run first time around, moved up again to apply pressure on the backstretch, headed that rival on the last turn, put a head in front at the quarter pole, lost command into the stretch and gave way.
